vernac_cmds: Definition stronger {t: type} (v v': reptype t) : Prop := forall sh, data_at sh t v |-- data_at sh t v'.
Definition data_equal {t} v1 v2 := forall sh, data_at sh t v1 = data_at sh t v2.
Notation "X '>>>' Y" := (stronger X Y) (at level 60, no associativity).
Notation "X '===' Y" := (data_equal X Y) (at level 60, no associativity).
Lemma stronger_refl: forall t (v: reptype t), v >>> v.
Lemma stronger_JMeq: forall t t' a a' b b', t=t' -> @JMeq (reptype t) a (reptype t') a' -> @JMeq (reptype t) b (reptype t') b' -> a >>> b -> a' >>> b'.
Lemma eq_rect_r_stronger: forall {t1 t2} v0 v1 (H: t1 = t2), v0 >>> v1 -> eq_rect_r reptype v0 H >>> eq_rect_r reptype v1 H.
Lemma stronger_trans: forall t (v0 v1 v2: reptype t), v0 >>> v1 -> v1 >>> v2 -> v0 >>> v2.
Lemma field_at_stronger: forall sh t gfs v0 v1, v0 >>> v1 -> field_at sh t gfs v0 |-- field_at sh t gfs v1.

Lemma stronger_array_ext: forall t0 n a (v0 v1: reptype (Tarray t0 n a)), Zlength (unfold_reptype v0) = Zlength (unfold_reptype v1) -> (forall i, 0 <= i < n -> Znth i (unfold_reptype v0) >>> Znth i (unfold_reptype v1)) -> v0 >>> v1.
rewrite Z.max_r in H2 by omega.
rewrite Z2Nat.id in H3 by omega.
assert (field_compatible t0 nil (offset_val (sizeof t0 * i) p)).
assert (sizeof t0 = 0) by (pose proof (sizeof_pos t0); omega).
apply align_compatible_rec_Tarray_inv with (i:=i) in H2; auto.
assert (H5: 0 <= sizeof t0 * i < sizeof t0 * n).
replace 0 with (sizeof t0 * 0)%Z by (rewrite Z.mul_0_r; auto).
rewrite Z.max_r in H1 by omega.
assert (sizeof t0 * i + sizeof t0 <= sizeof t0 * n).
apply align_compatible_rec_Tarray_inv with (i:=i) in H2; auto.
unfold nested_field_offset, nested_field_type in H0; simpl in H0.
Lemma stronger_default_val: forall t v, v >>> default_val t.

Lemma stronger_proj_reptype: forall t v1 v2, (v1 >>> v2) <-> (forall gfs, legal_nested_field t gfs -> type_is_by_value (nested_field_type t gfs) = true -> proj_reptype t gfs v1 >>> proj_reptype t gfs v2).
unfold nested_field_offset in H; simpl in H.
unfold nested_field_type in H; simpl in H.
Lemma data_equal_stronger: forall {t} (v1 v2: reptype t), (v1 === v2) <-> (v1 >>> v2) /\ (v2 >>> v1).
split; intro sh; rewrite H; auto.
intro sh; apply pred_ext; [apply H | apply H0].
Lemma data_equal_JMeq: forall t t' a a' b b', t=t' -> @JMeq (reptype t) a (reptype t') a' -> @JMeq (reptype t) b (reptype t') b' -> a === b -> a' === b'.
Lemma eq_rect_r_data_equal: forall {t1 t2} v0 v1 (H: t1 = t2), v0 === v1 -> eq_rect_r reptype v0 H === eq_rect_r reptype v1 H.
Lemma data_equal_refl': forall t (v v': reptype t), v = v' -> v === v'.
Lemma field_at_data_equal: forall sh t gfs v0 v1, v0 === v1 -> field_at sh t gfs v0 = field_at sh t gfs v1.
Instance Proper_field_at: forall sh t gfs, Proper ((@data_equal _) ==> eq) (field_at sh t gfs).

Lemma data_equal_array_ext: forall t0 n a (v0 v1: reptype (Tarray t0 n a)), Zlength (unfold_reptype v0) = Zlength (unfold_reptype v1) -> (forall i, 0 <= i < n -> Znth i (unfold_reptype v0) === Znth i (unfold_reptype v1)) -> v0 === v1.
apply data_equal_stronger; split; apply stronger_array_ext; auto.
destruct (data_equal_stronger (Znth i (unfold_reptype v0)) (Znth i (unfold_reptype v1))) as [? _].
destruct (data_equal_stronger (Znth i (unfold_reptype v0)) (Znth i (unfold_reptype v1))) as [? _].

Lemma data_equal_proj_reptype: forall t v1 v2, (v1 === v2) <-> (forall gfs, legal_nested_field t gfs -> type_is_by_value (nested_field_type t gfs) = true -> proj_reptype t gfs v1 === proj_reptype t gfs v2).

assert ((forall gfs : list gfield, legal_nested_field t gfs -> type_is_by_value (nested_field_type t gfs) = true -> proj_reptype t gfs v1 === proj_reptype t gfs v2) <-> (forall gfs : list gfield, legal_nested_field t gfs -> type_is_by_value (nested_field_type t gfs) = true -> proj_reptype t gfs v1 >>> proj_reptype t gfs v2) /\ (forall gfs : list gfield, legal_nested_field t gfs -> type_is_by_value (nested_field_type t gfs) = true -> proj_reptype t gfs v2 >>> proj_reptype t gfs v1)).
rewrite data_equal_stronger; split; apply H; auto.
Notation "X '>>>' Y" := (stronger X Y) (at level 60, no associativity).
Notation "X '===' Y" := (data_equal X Y) (at level 60, no associativity).
